This paper discusses the use of social media for the dissemination of public health messages, which falls under the category of social media and its impact on society (cs.SI). The study also involves the use of a bespoke Twitter platform, which could be categorized under cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY). The study uses a quasi-experimental design and involves data analysis, which could be categorized under computational experiments (cs.CE) and statistical methods (cs.SD). Finally, the study focuses on health behavior change, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
